    'en' => '<div class="space-y-6"><div><h4 class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">1. How to Download the File</h4><p class="text-muted-foreground mb-2">To avoid any issues, please follow these exact steps:</p><ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-muted-foreground"><li>Open the link above.</li><li>You\'ll see a Google Drive folder with your purchased stickers file.</li></ul><div class="bg-green-950/30 rounded-xl p-6 border-2 border-green-800 mt-4"><p class="text-yellow-500 font-semibold mb-2">⚠ VERY IMPORTANT:</p><ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-muted-foreground"><li>Download the entire folder or file completely.</li><li>Click the file, then tap the <strong class="text-foreground">Download icon</strong> at the top right.</li></ul></div></div><div><h4 class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">2. How to Import the Stickers to Your reMarkable Device</h4><p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">You can use one of two methods to upload the .rmdoc file to your reMarkable device:</p><div class="bg-muted/30 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4"><p class="text-primary font-semibold mb-2">Method 1 – Drag & Drop via reMarkable Desktop App (for Windows & macOS)</p><ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1 text-muted-foreground"><li>Open the <strong class="text-foreground">reMarkable Desktop App</strong>.</li><li><strong class="text-foreground">Drag and drop</strong> the .rmdoc file directly into the app window.</li><li>It will automatically upload and sync to your device.</li></ol><div class="bg-yellow-950/30 border border-yellow-800 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4"><p class="text-yellow-500 font-semibold mb-2">⚠ IMPORTANT:</p><ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-muted-foreground"><li>Do not use the "Import" button — it doesn\'t support .rmdoc files. Only drag and drop works.</li><li>Do not use the mobile app, as it does not support drag-and-drop.</li></ul></div></div><div class="bg-muted/30 rounded-lg p-4"><p class="text-primary font-semibold mb-2">Method 2 – USB Transfer via Web Interface</p><ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1 text-muted-foreground"><li>Connect your reMarkable to your computer with a <strong class="text-foreground">USB cable</strong>.</li><li>On your reMarkable, go to <strong class="text-foreground">Settings → Storage → Enable USB Web Interface</strong>.</li><li>On your computer, open a web browser and go to this address: <code class="bg-muted/30 px-1 rounded text-foreground">http://10.11.99.1</code></li><li>You will see your device files.</li><li>Use the <strong class="text-foreground">import button</strong>.</li><li>Done! Your file is now on your device.</li></ol><p class="text-muted-foreground mt-4">💡 <em>You don\'t need Wi-Fi for this — just the USB cable.</em></p></div></div><div class="bg-green-950/30 rounded-xl p-6 border-2 border-green-800 mt-4"><p class="text-primary font-semibold mb-2">📧 Need Help?</p><p class="text-muted-foreground">If you experience any issue — whether downloading or uploading the file — please don\'t hesitate to contact me at <a href="mailto:info.norphis@gmail.com" class="text-primary hover:underline">info.norphis@gmail.com</a>.</p><p class="text-muted-foreground">I\'ll get back to you within 24 hours max, usually much faster.</p><p class="text-muted-foreground">Thank you again, and enjoy your new template!</p></div></div>',
    'de' => '<div class="space-y-6"><div><h4 class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">1. Datei herunterladen</h4><p class="text-muted-foreground mb-2">Befolge diese Schritte, um Probleme zu vermeiden:</p><ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-muted-foreground"><li>Öffne den Link oben.</li><li>Du siehst einen Google Drive-Ordner mit deiner gekauften Datei.</li></ul><div class="bg-green-950/30 rounded-xl p-6 border-2 border-green-800 mt-4"><p class="text-yellow-500 font-semibold mb-2">⚠ SEHR WICHTIG:</p><ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-muted-foreground"><li>Lade den gesamten Ordner oder die Datei vollständig herunter.</li><li>Klicke auf die Datei, dann auf das <strong class="text-foreground">Download-Symbol</strong> oben rechts.</li></ul></div></div><div><h4 class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">2. Template auf dein reMarkable importieren</h4><p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">Du kannst eine von zwei Methoden verwenden, um die .rmdoc-Datei hochzuladen:</p><div class="bg-muted/30 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4"><p class="text-primary font-semibold mb-2">Methode 1 – Drag & Drop über reMarkable Desktop-App (Windows & macOS)</p><ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1 text-muted-foreground"><li>Öffne die <strong class="text-foreground">reMarkable Desktop-App</strong>.</li><li><strong class="text-foreground">Ziehe die .rmdoc-Datei</strong> direkt ins App-Fenster.</li><li>Sie wird automatisch hochgeladen und synchronisiert.</li></ol><div class="bg-yellow-950/30 border border-yellow-800 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4"><p class="text-yellow-500 font-semibold mb-2">⚠ WICHTIG:</p><ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-muted-foreground"><li>Verwende nicht den "Importieren"-Button — er unterstützt keine .rmdoc-Dateien.</li><li>Verwende nicht die mobile App, sie unterstützt kein Drag-and-Drop.</li></ul></div></div><div class="bg-muted/30 rounded-lg p-4"><p class="text-primary font-semibold mb-2">Methode 2 – USB-Übertragung über Web-Interface</p><ol class=